              },
              "free_text": [
                " In the 13 up to 20 MeV energy region.",
                "Incident energies of deuteron beams were 2 and 3 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " In order to reduce effect of low-energy",
                "neutrons on activation cross-section measurement,",
                "following technics were used:",
                " - The new D target was used (1.5 mg/cm2 instead",
                "   1.7 mg/cm2).",
                " - In the neutron energy region from 1 to 6 MeV,",
                "   the irradiation time for neutrons was as short",
                "   as possible.",
                " - In the 7 to 13 MeV energy region, the",
                "   measuring neutron flux was deducted from the curve",
                "   of the effective reaction threshold energy via the",
                "   measured neutron flux. The curve was obtained by",
                "   irradiating a set of samples with different reaction",
                "   threshold energies.",
                " - In the 13 to 20 MeV energy",
                "   region, the effect of low-energy neutrons was",
                "   deducted by irradiating an empty target that was",
                "   free of T.",
                "Neutron spectra for the D(d,n)He-3 and T(d,n)He-4",
                "reactions at the 0-degree angle have been measured",
                "by the time-of-flying method for the deuteron beams",
                "of 2 and 3 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
